description.narrative: UNICEF, government and partners have strengthened capacity to generate, analyze and use rigorous evidence from equity-focused research and evaluation, for evidence-based policy advocacy and programming, which contributes to Evaluation, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Child rights and gender equality prioritized in evidence-based public discourse, national policies, budget allocations, legislation, and social protection systems and progressively promoted and protected in social and cultural attitudes, practices and norms, with a focus on the most vulnerable

description.narrative: The evidence agenda at ACO has been further institutionalized through the development of substantive Evidence SOPs that provide formal technical and procedural guidance for the conduct of evaluations, research and studies. 3 key evaluations, including strategic positioning and thematic evaluations, have been completed, with one still underway. Overall implementation of evaluation management response stands at 75 percent. ;Furthermore, utilization of evidence, particularly in the case of the Strategic Positioning Evaluation that’ll will inform the design of the next Country Programme Document, has been further strengthened through the management response mechanism. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/01/2022
